An air pollution monitoring system is crucial for assessing air quality and understanding the environmental impact. It helps track pollutant levels, identify problem areas, and inform necessary actions to improve air quality and public health. Regular data collection and analysis are essential for effective policymaking and implementing measures to reduce pollution and its adverse effects on society and the ecosystem

A smart parking system is a highly efficient and technology-driven solution that optimizes parking spaces, making it easier for users to find available spots and reducing congestion in parking lots. It uses sensors, cameras, and data analytics to monitor parking space occupancy and provide real-time information to drivers. This can lead to reduced traffic, lower carbon emissions, and improved overall parking management.
